The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                              
	Calcutta, Dec. 8: Five teachers of Sarisha Ramakrishna Mission Sarada Mandir in Diamond Harbour, who had told police they will not wear the regulation white saris to school from December 8, were not allowed to sign the staff register. They were wearing coloured saris today. We were not allowed to sign the register and we may be assaulted by a section of teachers and parents, said Jayotee Mitra, one of the teachers.                  
	Calcutta: Suhrid Dutta and Debu Malik, awarded life sentence in the Tapasi Malik murder case, have appealed before Calcutta High Court challenging the verdict.                                                                                                                         
